**Key insight:** We query `lungCancer` while conditioning/intervening on `cough`.

- **`original`**: P(lungCancer) ≈ 0.01 (base rate)
- **`conditioning`**: P(lungCancer | cough=true) is much higher (~0.13), because observing cough is true provides evidence that at least one of its causes (cold or lungCancer) is true
- **`intervention`**: P(lungCancer | do(cough=true)) ≈ 0.01, unchanged! Intervening breaks the causal link—forcing cough to be true tells us nothing about the underlying causes

This demonstrates the fundamental difference: conditioning on the effect makes the causes dependent (through the collider), while intervention blocks this information flow.

